romatic, with ṣād. But the right form is سَلِيخَة (salīḵa) with sīn. And in what concerns the سَلِيخَة (salīḵa, “peel”) which the vulgar hotes هَيْدُورة (haydūra) this isn’t even from the speech of the Arabs, they say it for the hide that the flayer strips off."}]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "See أُهْبَة (ʔuhba)."}, "ipa": ["/ʔi.haːb/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n1428", "headword_ar": "اـِهَابٌ", "root": "Ahb", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A skin,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hide,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, Msb, K,) in an absolute sense, (A,) of a bull or cow, sheep or goat, or wild animal: (TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a skin,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hide, not yet tanned:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K:) and sometimes applied to the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "skin"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a man: (Msb:) pl. (of pauc., TA)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A=hibapN", "text_ar": "ا=هِبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAar, K) and (of mult., TA)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^uhubN", "text_ar": "اُهُبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, A, Mgh, Msb, Msb, K,) with two dammehs, (Mgh, Msb,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^habN", "text_ar": "اهَبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb, K,) contr. to rule, (S, Msb,) or, accord. to Sb, (L,) this last is a quasi-pl. n.: (Mgh, L:) in one copy of the K, it is written"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A=hub", "text_ar": "ا=هُب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jaAEuwA Hat~aY", "text_ar": "جَاعُوا حَتَّى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^akaluwA AlA^uhuba", "text_ar": "اَكَلُوا الاُهُبَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "They hungered so that they ate the skins,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hides"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaAda yaxoruju mino A_ihaAbihi", "text_ar": "كَادَ يَخْرُجُ مِنْ اـِهَابِهِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY Eadowihi", "text_ar": "فِى عَدْوِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He almost issued from his skin in his running"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Haqana Ald~imaA='a fiY A^uhubihaA", "text_ar": "حَقَنَ الدِّمَا=ءَ فِى اُهُبِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He spared the people's blood in their bodies"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA, from a trad.)"}], "source_refs": ["A", "Msb", "K", "TA", "S", "Mgh", "IAar", "L"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}